present the results of the two other scenarios: competition with blue H2
(Supplementary Fig. 28) and an operating constraint on electrolysers (Supplementary Fig. 29). Figure 5 highlights the emissions and cost impact of an annual
VRE requirement in serving non-H2 load that is above the optimal level
(vis-à-vis the objective function). This policy scenario is most relevant under annual time matching and the ‘compete’ additionality framework
